article.headline: Wyoming drops No. 23 TCU behind Zavecz's 20 points
article.linkText: Wyoming drops No. 23 TCU behind Zavecz's 20 points
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Hanna Zavecz scored 20 points and pulled down nine rebounds in leading Wyoming to a 66-51 win over TCU on Saturday.

Zavecz hit a 3-pointer with 13:23 left to put the Cowgirls (12-5, 3-2 Mountain West Conference) ahead 40-38.

Wyoming kept out of reach when TCU (13-6, 3-2) went 4 minutes without scoring. Helen Roden broke the drought with two free throws but Zavecz made another 3-pointer to put Wyoming up by 10.

The Cowgirls finished by making 6 of 6 free throws.

Wyoming entered the second half ahead 28-26 after a back-and-forth first half.

After Zavecz, Dominique Sisk scored 18 points for Wyoming. TCU was led by Ashley Davis' 13 points and Adrianne Ross' 11.
